decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - The development hereby permitted shall begin not later than three years from the date of this decision. 
Condition : 2 - The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans and specifications: [Site Plan & Images A02439, Cover Letter dated on 21st February 2024, Appendix A Unit Distribution, Appendix B Communication Hub Unit Management Plan Appendix C Sustainability, Appendix D Pavement Reinstatement, Power of the Public Screen leaflet, Communication Hub Unit Management Plan Received 27/02/2024].
Reason: In order to ensure the development is carried out in accordance with the planning permission.
Condition : 3 - The illuminated advertisement hereby approved shall comply with the following terms:
	
(a)	Between the hours of sunset and 23:00, the intensity of the illumination of the advertisement shall not exceed 300 cd/m2;
(b)	Between the hours of 23:00 and 06:00, the advertisement screen shall be switched off;
(c)	The advertisement shall be fitted with a light intensity monitoring censor to ensure the illuminance intensity is dimmable to take account of ambient light conditions and comply with the maximum recommended lighting intensity; 
(d)	The advertisement shall not display any moving, or apparently moving, images; 
(e)	Any change in the advertisement display shall be instantaneous;
(f)	The advertisements displayed shall not change more frequently than once every 60 seconds.
Reason: In the interests of amenity and highway safety.
